overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, moving away from a generic look to a more polished and
  calming design. The agent began by analyzing the existing codebase,
  identifying areas for improvement in color, layout, and component styling. A
  new sleep-themed color palette was introduced, along with redesigned form
  layouts, enhanced UI components (checkboxes, sliders, progress bars), and a
  more visually appealing intro section. All questionnaire sections were updated
  to ensure consistent styling. During the process, a console error related to
  null input values in form fields was identified and fixed by modifying the
  Input component. Further aesthetic refinements were made to alert colors and
  the inconsistent card header gradients in the report section, ensuring a
  cohesive visual experience throughout the application. The changes were
  meticulously applied and committed in logical, atomic groups.
